04/05/2010
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Slovenian officer David Humar took over the command of NATO headquarters in Skopje from Bulgarian Commodore Valentin Gagashev on Monday (May 3rd).
During the ceremony, Humar said the long-standing name dispute with Greece is a political obstacle to Macedonia's Euro-Atlantic integration and voiced hope that the problem will be resolved.
Chief of General Staff of the Macedonian Army, General Miroslav Stojanovski, said his country will continue implementing reforms needed to join the Alliance.
(Makfax, STA - 03/05/10)
